  "name": "Morrison COU1 — CPB hemolysis credibility assessment",
  "description": "V&V 40 credibility assessment for CFD hemolysis prediction of the FDA generic centrifugal blood pump under cardiopulmonary bypass (CPB) conditions. COU1 evaluates whether the computational model can identify worst-case hemolysis operating conditions for a Class II CPB device at Model Risk Level 2. Full 13-factor assessment: 7 factors assessed (all meeting required levels), 6 factors not assessed (acceptable at MRL 2). The safety analysis requires that the model demonstrate bounded shear-stress exposure time: specifically, all blood-contacting flow paths must not expose erythrocytes to shear stress exceeding 150 Pa for durations greater than 700 ms, a threshold established from clinical haemolysis onset data. This sub-lethal shear-time integral constraint is central to patient safety and is referenced throughout the validation narrative and sensitivity studies.",
  "assuranceLevel": "Medium",
  "couName": "CPB use",
  "decision": "Accepted",
  "deviceClass": "Class II",
  "modelRiskLevel": 2,
  "bindsRequirement": "https://uofa.net/synth/req/cpb-hemolysis-req-set-001",
  "bindsClaim": "https://uofa.net/synth/claim/cpb-hemolysis-claim-001",
